HEADWORD: Orphanage
<hw>Or"phan*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being an orphan; orphanhood; orphans, collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An institution or asylum for the care of
orphans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orphancy</ent>⟦br⟧
